Despite the witness of these manuscripts, however, we believe that the hymn isa distinctively Celtic composition, and is not the work either of St. Prosper of Aquitaine or of Julianus Pomerius. The genuine works of Prosper arc quite different in character, both as regards form and matter. The style of that writer has no resemblance to the rude and barbarous, though vigorous, Latin of this hymn; and the speculations as to the ermion and the fall of the ‘giants' are foreign to his ways of thinking.
